title: Bug 121170: get column label from meta data object should return user recognizable strings
description: The bug report is missing a description of the issue. However, based on the title and the expected behavior mentioned in the EB section, it can be inferred that there is an issue with the getColumnLabel() method in the IMetaData object. This method is expected to return user recognizable strings for the column labels.
OB: The observed behavior is not provided in the bug report.
EB: Bug 121170: The getColumnLabel() method in the IMetaData object should return user recognizable strings.
SR:
To reproduce the issue:
1. Call IMetaData.getColumnLabel() before data extraction.
2. Call IMetaData.getColumnLabel() after data extraction.
3. Compare the results and observe the difference in returned values.
